This paper discusses the evaluation of word embedding models for natural language processing applications, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
